entries.femaleVariant: [Give cigarette] Fine, here.
Fine, here.
Fwoo, uh... bum a cig?
Can't believe she gave up.
I can't wrap my head around it... Never saw Evelyn as the type to give up...
entries.maleVariant: Can't wrap my head around it... I never saw Evelyn as the type to give up...

entries.femaleVariant: C'mon, what she went through? I wouldn't call it giving up.
Stay strong.
I dunno know what to say. Never was any good at this stuff.
Ah, you don't need to talk. Did more for her than anyone else.
I had a motive to find her, Judy. You know that.
Yeah, maybe. Just never imagined she'd choose this.
Didn't know you smoked.
Uhh. Quit, been years. But right now I need something 'sides air in my lungs. Please, V, just one.
Sorry. Out.
No can do.
Sorry, no can do.
Sorry, fresh out.
That was her smoke case.
Wanna hold on to it?
No, you seem to like it, keep it.
Want it back?
She smoked some strange brand.
Shit try, V. I know you're not.
How?
Don't piss me off, not now.
She smoked some strange, boutique brand.
That's Evie. Whenever she pulled on a new face, it was down to the details.
Kinda glad it's you that has it, actually.
No, nobody.
Cheapskate.
You could get hooked again – I don't want that on me.
V, just give me a fucking smoke.
Dunno what to say.
It's what you bring that counts. You gave her the freedom to choose.
Stay strong, Judy. Don't let this tear you down.
Know what? Let's just not say anything for a minute, 'K?
Fuck, Evie...
I let her down. I thought if I gave her some space or time she'd get back on her feet…
'Member Fingers, how he said Evie was with 'im for four days?
Mhm... did say so.
She disappeared from Clouds a week before you turned up, Tom told me later. Couldn't sleep at night, knowin' that.
Kept thinking – what the hell happened to those other three days, so... I did some more diggin' in her virtus. Ehh – found Woodman.
He kept her. Had his way with her. The things he did... And once he got bored, he pawned her off.
Good thing I killed him.
So you found other recordings?
What'd Woodman do?
What'd Woodman do to her? Did you see it?
Wait, so you found other recordings?
Gotta be somethin' I can do about it.
Like what?
Don't know yet. Think I'll call Suze... Hehh, thanks, V. Sorry, but, uh, I'd rather be alone now. Promise to keep in touch.
Yeah... and I really wish I could unsee it.
Had another look at the corrupted ones. Lots of static – hard to pick up anything, really.
At some point I... stumbled on something like an echo of the spat we'd had... Last time we saw each other. But I know she wasn't scrolling.
Maybe she recalled it later, relived it, almost?
Then why was it saved as a virtu?
Tsh, got no explanation for it.
Implant could've been on when... Y'know, as a defense mechanism – escapin' into the past so as not to live the present.
Lotta people know the real Evelyn, who she really was?
Anything comes up, holler on the holo.
[Stand] Anything comes up – call.
Sure you don't need anything?
No, but sweet of you to ask.
Had no idea he was such a monster.
Had no idea that guy was such a monster. Saw him as your average tricksy sleazebag.
Yeah, puts on a convincing facade. I knew him, but I never thought him that sick in the brain.
I zeroed Woodman. Didn't plan on it – just how the chips landed.
Glad I did, though.
Me too. I can't even imagine.
Still, it's not enough... There're so many more like him.
Sure you don't need anything?
Her condition – couldn't think about anything else… Tech-wise she was clean, doll shard was operational, uncorrupted…
So, psychological trauma – had to be that. Did some more diggin' in her virtus. Found Woodman.
